{
  "texts": [
    "This implementation results in a more efficient performance in teeth numbering and decay detection compared to the original YOLOv7 model.",
    "Additionally, an algorithm has been developed to assess teeth with caries by correlating the numbered teeth with the detected caries.",
    "Material and methods Sample size determinationThe determination of the sample size for the test dataset was performed with Fisher's exact test A design incorporating clustering was employed because of every digital bitewing radiograph contained averagely 16 surfaces which was calculated by design effect (DE).",
    "Design effect (DE), which assesses the performance of a particular sampling method compared to that of a simple random sample, is a valuable tool in considering the precision of a cluster sample.",
    "Equation of DE is 1 + (m-1) x ICC, in where m represents size of cluster, and ICC is the intraclass correlation coefficient."
  ]
}